NODE_1_length_685731_cov_56.949454	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	600	2492	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_00010;note=WP_000753855.1 choline-binding protein PcpA (Streptococcus pneumoniae) [pid:48.4%25%2C q_cov:38.1%25%2C s_cov:31.3%25%2C Eval:8.9e-62%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR04035%3B glucan_65_rpt: glucan-binding repeat [Name:TIGR04035%2C Eval:8.8e-34%2C score:113.5%2C bias:27.0],COG:COG5263 Glucan-binding domain (YG repeat)  [Category:G%2C Aligned:8-268%2C Eval:5.9e-44%2C score:156.9],Domain:cl27558:COG5263 Glucan-binding domain (YG repeat)  [Carbohydrate transport and metabolism]. This model describes a region of about 63 amino acids that is composed of three repeats of a more broadly distributed family of shorter repeats modeled by pfam01473. While the shorter repeats are often associated with choline binding (and therefore with cell wall binding)%2C the longer repeat described here represents a subgroup of repeat sequences associated with glucan binding%2C as found in a number glycosylhydrolases. Shah%2C et al. describe a repeat consensus%2C WYYFDANGKAVTGAQTINGQTLYFDQDGKQVKG%2C that corresponds to half of the repeat as modeled here and one and a half copies of the repeat as modeled by pfam01473. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:407-497%2C Eval:5.0e-18%2C score:82.6%2C C-term missing],COG:COG0791:Spr Cell wall-associated hydrolase%2C NlpC family [Category:M%2C Aligned:500-617%2C Eval:2.3e-10%2C score:57.7%2C N-term missing],MGA_1
