NODE_2_length_418668_cov_55.560609	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	199130	199501	.	-	0	ID=MGA_826;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MRAHAEAGDTVVVISATFEPIILRAMEHHPFDNQISTRMSVATDGTYTRAVEGLPVEGEEKLAAVRRFGDSRFGPGNWELAYAYGDHHSDRAVLSAAEHPRAVSPDRPLARTAREKGWEILDW;locus_tag=LOCUS_08210;note=WP_002225254.1 HAD family hydrolase (Neisseria) [pid:32.3%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:55.9%25%2C Eval:1.4e-10%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR01490%3B HAD-SF-IB-hyp1: HAD hydrolase%2C family IB [Name:TIGR01490%2C Eval:6.1e-23%2C score:80.1%2C bias:0.0],Domain:cl21460:HAD_like Haloacid Dehalogenase-like Hydrolases. This subfamily includes the uncharacterized Bacillus subtilis YhcW. It belongs to the beta-phosphoglucomutase-like family whose other members include Lactococcus lactis beta-PGM%2C a mutase which catalyzes the interconversion of beta-D-glucose 1-phosphate (G1P) and D-glucose 6-phosphate (G6P)%2C Saccharomyces cerevisiae phosphatases GPP1 and GPP2 that dephosphorylate DL-glycerol-3-phosphate and DOG1 and DOG2 that dephosphorylate 2-deoxyglucose-6-phosphate%2C and Escherichia coli 6-phosphogluconate phosphatase YieH. This family belongs to the haloacid dehalogenase-like (HAD) hydrolases%2C a large superfamily of diverse enzymes that catalyze carbon or phosphoryl group transfer reactions on a range of substrates%2C using an active site aspartate in nucleophilic catalysis. Members of this superfamily include 2-L-haloalkanoic acid dehalogenase%2C azetidine hydrolase%2C phosphonoacetaldehyde hydrolase%2C phosphoserine phosphatase%2C phosphomannomutase%2C P-type ATPases and many others. HAD hydrolases are found in all three kingdoms of life%2C and most genomes are predicted to contain multiple HAD-like proteins. Members possess a highly conserved alpha/beta core domain%2C and many also possess a small cap domain%2C the fold and function of which is variable. HAD hydrolases are sometimes referred to as belonging to the DDDD superfamily of phosphohydrolases. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:2-120%2C Eval:4.9e-20%2C score:78.5%2C N-term missing],MGA_826
