NODE_2_length_418668_cov_55.560609	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	228764	232468	.	-	0	ID=MGA_852;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_08470;note=WP_011029870.1 DNA helicase PcrA (Streptomyces) [pid:28.1%25%2C q_cov:35.2%25%2C s_cov:51.0%25%2C Eval:7.7e-31%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR01073%3B pcrA: ATP-dependent DNA helicase PcrA [Name:TIGR01073%2C Eval:7.4e-70%2C score:234.1%2C bias:0.0],Domain:cl28312:UvrD Superfamily I DNA or RNA helicase [Replication%2C recombination and repair]. AddAB%2C also called RexAB%2C substitutes for RecBCD in several bacterial lineages. These DNA recombination proteins act before synapse and are particularly important for DNA repair of double-stranded breaks by homologous recombination. The term AddAB is used broadly%2C with AddA homologous between the Firmicutes (as modeled here) and the alphaproteobacteria%2C while the partner AddB proteins show no strong homology across the two groups of species. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:21-949%2C Eval:3.2e-86%2C score:302.1],MGA_852
NODE_2_length_418668_cov_55.560609	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	232465	235371	.	-	0	ID=MGA_853;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_08480;note=TIGR:TIGR03623%3B TIGR03623: probable DNA repair protein [Name:TIGR03623%2C Eval:2.3e-15%2C score:53.8%2C bias:0.0],Domain:cl28251:AddB ATP-dependent helicase/DNAse subunit B [Replication%2C recombination and repair]. DNA repair is accomplished by several different systems in prokaryotes. Recombinational repair of double-stranded DNA breaks involves the RecBCD pathway in some lineages%2C and AddAB (also called RecAB) in other. The AddA protein is conserved between the firmicutes and the alphaproteobacteria%2C while the partner protein is not. The partner may be designated AddB%2C as in Bacillus and in alphaproteobacteria%2C or RexB as in Streptococcus and Lactococcus. Note%2C however%2C that RexB proteins lack an N-terminal GxxGxGK[ST] ATP-binding motif found in Bacillus subtilis and related species%2C and this difference may be important%3B this model represents specifically RexB proteins as found in Streptococcus and Lactococcus. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:658-831%2C Eval:8.6e-12%2C score:66.3%2C N-term missing],MGA_853
