NODE_2_length_418668_cov_55.560609	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	284151	284390	.	-	0	ID=MGA_903;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MSLGFYVDVQRCIGCRTCQVACKDRHNLQAAGPRTRRVGSFECGTYPEVGMFHLTVSCNHCDDPACVNAGRTRRWACSI;locus_tag=LOCUS_08980;note=WP_005814564.1 4Fe-4S dicluster domain-containing protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:55.2%25%2C q_cov:84.8%25%2C s_cov:34.6%25%2C Eval:1.9e-17%2C partial hit],internal stop codon at [284151:284153](-),frameshifted%2C insertion/deletion at around 284105,TIGR:TIGR02951%3B DMSO_dmsB: dimethylsulfoxide reductase%2C chain B [Name:TIGR02951%2C Eval:1.4e-21%2C score:75.2%2C bias:4.1],Domain:cl25360:DMSOR_beta-like Beta subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. This family consists of the small beta iron-sulfur (FeS) subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. Members of this family also contain a large%2C periplasmic molybdenum-containing alpha subunit and may have a small gamma subunit as well.  Examples of heterodimeric members with alpha and beta subunits include arsenite oxidase%2C and tungsten-containing formate dehydrogenase (FDH-T) while   heterotrimeric members containing alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits include formate dehydrogenase-N (FDH-N)%2C and nitrate reductase (NarGHI).  The beta subunit contains four Fe4/S4 and/or Fe3/S4 clusters which transfer the electrons from the alpha subunit to a hydrophobic integral membrane protein%2C presumably a cytochrome containing two b-type heme groups. The reducing equivalents are then transferred to menaquinone%2C which finally reduces the electron-accepting enzyme system. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-69%2C Eval:5.6e-15%2C score:63.2%2C C-term missing],MGA_903
