NODE_2_length_418668_cov_55.560609	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	317126	318274	.	+	0	ID=MGA_940;product=glycine amidinotransferase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_013228026.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_09350;note=WP_013228026.1 glycine amidinotransferase (Amycolatopsis mediterranei) [pid:41.8%25%2C q_cov:95.8%25%2C s_cov:98.1%25%2C Eval:1.6e-81],Domain:cl19186:Amidinotransf Amidinotransferase. Peptidyl-arginine deiminase (PAD) enzymes catalyze the deimination of the guanidino group from carboxy-terminal arginine residues of various peptides to produce ammonia. PAD from Porphyromonas gingivalis (PPAD) appears to be evolutionarily unrelated to mammalian PAD (pfam03068)%2C which is a metalloenzyme. PPAD is thought to belong to the same superfamily as aminotransferase and arginine deiminase%2C and to form an alpha/beta propeller structure. This family has previously been named PPADH (Porphyromonas peptidyl-arginine deiminase homologs). The predicted catalytic residues in PPAD are Asp130%2C Asp187%2C His236%2C Asp238 and Cys351. These are absolutely conserved with the exception of Asp187 which is absent in two family members. PPAD is also able to catalyze the deimination of free L-arginine%2C but has primarily peptidyl-arginine specificity. It may have a FMN cofactor. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:13-352%2C Eval:5.4e-14%2C score:68.5],MGA_940
