NODE_2_length_418668_cov_55.560609	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	326922	328430	.	+	0	ID=MGA_950;product=putative DNA modification/repair radical SAM protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_010966615.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_09450;note=WP_010966615.1 putative DNA modification/repair radical SAM protein (Clostridium) [pid:58.9%25%2C q_cov:81.7%25%2C s_cov:90.2%25%2C Eval:4.7e-132],Domain:cl28529:COG4277 Predicted DNA-binding protein with the Helix-hairpin-helix motif  [General function prediction only]. This uncharacterized protein of about 400 amino acids in length contains a radical SAM protein in the N-terminal half. Members are present in about twenty percent of prokaryotic genomes%2C always paired with a member of the conserved hypothetical protein TIGR03915. Roughly forty percent of the members of that family exist as fusions with a uracil-DNA glycosylase-like region%2C TIGR03914. In DNA%2C uracil results from deamidation of cytosine%2C forming U/G mismatches that lead to mutation%2C and so uracil-DNA glycosylase is a DNA repair enzyme. This indirect connection%2C and the recurring role or radical SAM protein in modification chemistries%2C suggest that this protein may act in DNA modification%2C repair%2C or both. [Unknown function%2C Enzymes of unknown specificity] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-411%2C Eval:0.0e+00%2C score:541.3],MGA_950
