NODE_2_length_418668_cov_55.560609	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	337091	338242	.	-	0	ID=MGA_958;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_09530;note=WP_010942870.1 DNA polymerase III subunit delta' (Geobacter sulfurreducens) [pid:33.1%25%2C q_cov:73.9%25%2C s_cov:89.2%25%2C Eval:7.2e-34%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR00678%3B holB: DNA polymerase III%2C delta' subunit [Name:TIGR00678%2C Eval:8.1e-55%2C score:183.3%2C bias:0.0],Domain:cl26247:DNA_pol3_delta2 DNA polymerase III%2C delta subunit. This model represents the well-conserved first ~ 365 amino acids of the translation of the dnaX gene. The full-length product of the dnaX gene in the model bacterium E. coli is the DNA polymerase III tau subunit. A translational frameshift leads to early termination and a truncated protein subunit gamma%2C about 1/3 shorter than tau and present in roughly equal amounts. This frameshift mechanism is not necessarily universal for species with DNA polymerase III but appears conserved in the exterme thermophile Thermus thermophilis. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-204%2C Eval:3.8e-45%2C score:159.9%2C C-term missing],COG:COG0470:HolB DNA polymerase III%2C delta prime subunit [Category:L%2C Aligned:138-312%2C Eval:2.6e-08%2C score:51.2],MGA_958
