NODE_2_length_418668_cov_55.560609	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	357769	358677	.	+	0	ID=MGA_980;product=class I SAM-dependent methyltransferase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_000903995.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_09750;note=WP_000903995.1 class I SAM-dependent methyltransferase (Enterobacteriaceae) [pid:26.1%25%2C q_cov:92.1%25%2C s_cov:92.6%25%2C Eval:2.5e-17],Domain:cl17173:AdoMet_MTases N/A. SAMBD is the domain at the N-terminus of proteins arginine methyltransferase 10 proteins. Protein arginine methyltransferases catalyze the transfer of methyl groups from S-adenosylmethionine - SAM - to arginine residues in target proteins thereby releasing S-adensoylhomocystein - SAH - as a product. Post-translational modification of arginine plays important roles in the eukaryotic cell such as signal transduction.This SAM-binding domain forms part of the catalytic core of the enzyme. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:57-117%2C Eval:4.4e-09%2C score:53.0%2C C-term missing],MGA_980
