NODE_3_length_368786_cov_57.202724	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	65271	66263	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1095;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_10890;note=WP_011706568.1 cytochrome c nitrite reductase subunit NrfD (Aeromonas hydrophila) [pid:26.6%25%2C q_cov:57.0%25%2C s_cov:54.3%25%2C Eval:4.2e-08%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR03148%3B cyt_nit_nrfD: cytochrome c nitrite reductase%2C NrfD subunit [Name:TIGR03148%2C Eval:2.4e-24%2C score:84.1%2C bias:23.1],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:4-315%2C Eval:7.1e-20%2C score:85.5],MGA_1095
