NODE_4_length_348023_cov_64.420950	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	67701	69452	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1455;product=FAD-binding protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_005809310.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_14480;note=WP_005809310.1 FAD-binding protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:40.4%25%2C q_cov:98.3%25%2C s_cov:99.1%25%2C Eval:5.2e-109],Domain:cl27630:FAD_binding_2 FAD binding domain. This model describes a family of redox proteins related to the succinate dehydrogenases and fumarate reductases of E. coli%2C mitochondria%2C and other well-characterized systems. A member of this family from Shewanella frigidimarina NCIMB400 is characterized as a water-soluble periplasmic protein with four heme groups%2C a non-covalently bound FAD%2C and essentially unidirectional fumarate reductase activity. At least seven distinct members of this family are found in Shewanella oneidensis%2C a species able to use a wide variety of pathways for respiraton. [Energy metabolism%2C Electron transport] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:83-579%2C Eval:2.0e-16%2C score:79.3%2C C-term missing],MGA_1455
