NODE_4_length_348023_cov_64.420950	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	70919	72091	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1457;product=iron-containing alcohol dehydrogenase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_003228872.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_14500;note=WP_003228872.1 iron-containing alcohol dehydrogenase (Bacillus) [pid:40.3%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:2.3e-83],Domain:cl02872:DHQ_Fe-ADH Dehydroquinate synthase-like (DHQ-like) and iron-containing alcohol dehydrogenases (Fe-ADH). The 3-dehydroquinate synthase EC:4.6.1.3 domain is present in isolation in various bacterial 3-dehydroquinate synthases and also present as a domain in the pentafunctional AROM polypeptide. 3-dehydroquinate (DHQ) synthase catalyzes the formation of dehydroquinate (DHQ) and orthophosphate from 3-deoxy-D-arabino heptulosonic 7 phosphate. This reaction is part of the shikimate pathway which is involved in the biosynthesis of aromatic amino acids. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-390%2C Eval:4.2e-151%2C score:429.4],MGA_1457
