NODE_4_length_348023_cov_64.420950	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	245058	245867	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1623;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MDIQWSLVLFTAIASCGTWVSVGVAVDELRGLTQRTNLVASVLALVLAVVGGIASVTHLSHPDRIMAVLSHPTAGIFLEALLIGLFIAAVAVYVILLKRDASAGARKAVAVLAAVIGIVFSFASGYSYMMEARTTWNTITLPLGYLGFGAASGLSLYLLLVACKKESAEAVKLAGLETVIGGVLALVSGLAFGFASGAATGDAAAIFWVALVCGGLAPLVCGWLARSKPASAVTMATVAFAGGIIGSIAFRAVMWMVGTAVANYFGIVL;locus_tag=LOCUS_16160;note=Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-262%2C Eval:3.8e-13%2C score:65.0],MGA_1623
NODE_4_length_348023_cov_64.420950	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	246028	246696	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1624;product=molecular chaperone TorD family protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_101723767.1;translation=MEQHDREELAEVNAARKGFYEFLASMYKLELTDEQIGTLTKQDLPTDAEYVGAGYATVKEYLRHRDSGTRQELAVDYARVFLCAGMYEQLMAPPYESVYTSEEHLLMQDARDSAVAFYLGEELGLPADNTTPEDHLSFEFQFMAKLIERAGAALDAGDEARYAELCAKQRAFFDEHLANWVPRLCADVRAYAQTAFYRGVADITEGFLQLEDQMIGQSAQAA;locus_tag=LOCUS_16170;note=WP_101723767.1 molecular chaperone TorD family protein (Eggerthella timonensis) [pid:33.0%25%2C q_cov:95.5%25%2C s_cov:93.9%25%2C Eval:6.5e-24],Domain:cl00958:Nitrate_red_del Nitrate reductase delta subunit. Type II members of the DMSO reductase family are heterotrimeric proteins with bis(molybdopterin guanine dinucleotide)Mo%2C iron-sulfur%2C and heme b prosthetic groups bound by the alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits respectively. Members of this protein family are not part of the mature protein%2C although they are the product of a fourth clustered gene. Proteins in this family are interpreted as a chaperone%2C analogous to NarJ of nitrate reductases. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:20-213%2C Eval:1.4e-20%2C score:82.8],MGA_1624
NODE_4_length_348023_cov_64.420950	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	246700	247335	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1625;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MAAYTRRAFAGFCGAAAVFAAFGGAVKAADGASETALVRPPGAQDELHLLASCVKCDRCRSVCHTGVIGVAEVGDGFLRARTPKLNFHRGSCDFCGDCQRVCPTGAIGAFDPEADKMGMAVVQKDRCVAYYQGCVECQKACPFEAIALDGDGHPVVDADRCNGCGVCEDVCPALVYRSFSGGTRRGIVVVSPSAYARLGKTVVEDESEMSA;locus_tag=LOCUS_16180;note=WP_015943352.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:38.5%25%2C q_cov:66.4%25%2C s_cov:30.2%25%2C Eval:3.8e-23%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR00402%3B napF: ferredoxin-type protein NapF [Name:TIGR00402%2C Eval:3.1e-23%2C score:80.3%2C bias:10.6],Domain:cl25974:Fer4_21 4Fe-4S dicluster domain. The six subunit complex RnfABCDGE in Rhodobacter capsulatus encodes an apparent NADH oxidoreductase responsible for electron transport to nitrogenase%2C necessary for nitrogen fixation. A closely related complex in E. coli%2C RsxABCDGE (Reducer of SoxR)%2C reduces the 2Fe-2S-containing superoxide sensor SoxR%2C active as a transcription factor when oxidized. This family of putative NADH oxidoreductase complexes exists in many of the same species as the related NQR%2C a Na(+)-translocating NADH-quinone reductase%2C but is distinct. This model describes the B subunit. [Energy metabolism%2C Electron transport] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:119-172%2C Eval:2.5e-10%2C score:55.8%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl27605:NIR_SIR Nitrite and sulphite reductase 4Fe-4S domain. Dissimilatory sulfite reductase catalyzes the six-electron reduction of sulfite to sulfide%2C as the terminal reaction in dissimilatory sulfate reduction. It remains unclear however%2C whether trithionate and thiosulfate serve as intermediate compounds to sulfide%2C or as end products of sulfite reduction. Sulfite reductase is a multisubunit enzyme composed of dimers of either alpha/beta or alpha/beta/gamma subunits%2C each containing a siroheme and iron sulfur cluster prosthetic center. Found in sulfate-reducing bacteria%2C these genes are commonly located in an unidirectional gene cluster. This model describes the alpha subunit of sulfite reductase. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Sulfur metabolism] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:97-208%2C Eval:2.4e-08%2C score:50.0%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl25361:NuoI Formate hydrogenlyase subunit 6/NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase 23 kD subunit (chain I) [Energy production and conversion]. See for descriptions of different groups. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:53-107%2C Eval:7.4e-08%2C score:47.4%2C C-term missing],MGA_1625
