NODE_6_length_180618_cov_59.035709	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	102437	103336	.	+	0	ID=MGA_2026;product=dimethyl sulfoxide reductase anchor subunit;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_005809896.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_20180;EC_number=1.8.5.3;note=WP_005809896.1 dimethyl sulfoxide reductase anchor subunit (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:25.1%25%2C q_cov:98.3%25%2C s_cov:97.2%25%2C Eval:1.9e-09],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-288%2C Eval:5.1e-10%2C score:56.3],MGA_2026
