NODE_7_length_163110_cov_60.318126	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	142607	143791	.	-	0	ID=MGA_2209;product=4Fe-4S binding protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_010888504.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_22010;note=WP_010888504.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Deinococcus radiodurans) [pid:26.8%25%2C q_cov:85.3%25%2C s_cov:91.9%25%2C Eval:1.3e-14],Domain:cl27605:NIR_SIR Nitrite and sulphite reductase 4Fe-4S domain. Dissimilatory sulfite reductase catalyzes the six-electron reduction of sulfite to sulfide%2C as the terminal reaction in dissimilatory sulfate reduction. It remains unclear however%2C whether trithionate and thiosulfate serve as intermediate compounds to sulfide%2C or as end products of sulfite reduction. Sulfite reductase is a multisubunit enzyme composed of dimers of either alpha/beta or alpha/beta/gamma subunits%2C each containing a siroheme and iron sulfur cluster prosthetic center. Found in sulfate-reducing bacteria%2C these genes are commonly located in an unidirectional gene cluster. This model describes the alpha subunit of sulfite reductase. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Sulfur metabolism] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:35-79%2C Eval:7.0e-09%2C score:53.9%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl25361:NuoI Formate hydrogenlyase subunit 6/NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase 23 kD subunit (chain I) [Energy production and conversion]. See for descriptions of different groups. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:286-372%2C Eval:2.6e-08%2C score:50.1%2C N-term missing],MGA_2209
