NODE_9_length_104966_cov_34.388201	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	33862	34803	.	+	0	ID=MGA_2415;product=polysulfide reductase NrfD;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_005811186.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_24050;gene=nrfD;note=WP_005811186.1 polysulfide reductase NrfD (Desulfitobacterium) [pid:24.5%25%2C q_cov:94.9%25%2C s_cov:94.6%25%2C Eval:1.5e-12],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:49-303%2C Eval:2.7e-09%2C score:54.3],MGA_2415
