NODE_9_length_104966_cov_34.388201	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	83329	83574	.	+	0	ID=MGA_2469;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MDVSCGICHGEGCRFCKGTGWLEILGCGMVDPNVLSMSGIDPEKYSGFAFGMGVERIACLKYNVPDLRMLVEGDMRFLRQF;locus_tag=LOCUS_24590;note=WP_011393252.1 phenylalanine--tRNA ligase subunit alpha (Moorella thermoacetica) [pid:69.1%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:23.8%25%2C Eval:3.7e-29%2C partial hit],frameshifted%2C insertion/deletion at around 83281,TIGR:TIGR00468%3B pheS: phenylalanine--tRNA ligase%2C alpha subunit [Name:TIGR00468%2C Eval:4.3e-25%2C score:86.6%2C bias:0.0],Domain:cl27322:PheS Phenylalanyl-tRNA synthetase alpha subunit [Translation%2C ribosomal structure and biogenesis]. Most phenylalanyl-tRNA synthetases are heterodimeric%2C with 2 alpha (pheS) and 2 beta (pheT) subunits. This model describes the alpha subunit%2C which shows some similarity to class II aminoacyl-tRNA ligases. Mitochondrial phenylalanyl-tRNA synthetase is a single polypeptide chain%2C active as a monomer%2C and similar to this chain rather than to the beta chain%2C but excluded from this model. An interesting feature of the alignment of all sequences captured by this model is a deep split between non-spirochete bacterial examples and all other examples%3B supporting this split is a relative deletion of about 50 residues in the former set between two motifs well conserved throughout the alignment. [Protein synthesis%2C tRNA aminoacylation] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-80%2C Eval:2.8e-39%2C score:129.3%2C N-term missing],MGA_2469
