NODE_46_length_10276_cov_57.160408	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	248	1858	.	-	0	ID=MGA_3238;product=MFS transporter;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_048065424.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_32060;note=WP_048065424.1 MFS transporter (Methanosarcina acetivorans) [pid:26.3%25%2C q_cov:93.1%25%2C s_cov:98.5%25%2C Eval:1.3e-42],Domain:cl26210:MFS_2 MFS/sugar transport protein. The Glycoside-Pentoside-Hexuronide (GPH):Cation Symporter Family (TC 2.A.2) GPH:cation symporters catalyze uptake of sugars in symport with a monovalent cation (H+ or Na+). Members of this family includes transporters for melibiose%2C lactose%2C raffinose%2C glucuronides%2C pentosides and isoprimeverose. Mutants of two groups of these symporters (the melibiose permeases of enteric bacteria%2C and the lactose permease of Streptococcus thermophilus) have been isolated in which altered cation specificity is observed or in which sugar transport is uncoupled from cation symport (i.e.%2C uniport is catalyzed). The various members of the family can use Na+%2C H+ or Li%2C Na+ or Li+%2C H+ or Li+%2C or only H+ as the symported cation. All of these proteins possess twelve putative transmembrane a-helical spanners. [Transport and binding proteins%2C Carbohydrates%2C organic alcohols%2C and acids] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:310-443%2C Eval:7.2e-08%2C score:51.9%2C N-term missing],MGA_3238
