NODE_53_length_8639_cov_6.115160	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	2551	3450	.	+	0	ID=MGA_3291;product=site-specific integrase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011861579.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_32560;note=WP_011861579.1 site-specific integrase (Clostridioides difficile) [pid:23.3%25%2C q_cov:92.6%25%2C s_cov:80.4%25%2C Eval:2.0e-19],Domain:cl28330:XerC Integrase [Replication%2C recombination and repair%2C Mobilome: prophages%2C transposons]. The phage integrase family describes a number of recombinases with tyrosine active sites that transiently bind covalently to DNA. Many are associated with mobile DNA elements%2C including phage%2C transposons%2C and phase variation loci. This model represents XerD%2C one of two closely related chromosomal proteins along with XerC (TIGR02224). XerC and XerD are site-specific recombinases which help resolve chromosome dimers to monomers for cell division after DNA replication. In species with a large chromosome and with homologs of XerD on other replicons%2C the chomosomal copy was preferred for building this model. This model does not detect all XerD%2C as some apparent XerD examples score below the trusted and noise cutoff scores. XerC and XerD interact with cell division protein FtsK. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:40-265%2C Eval:8.2e-16%2C score:73.4],MGA_3291
