NODE_74_length_6061_cov_60.384693	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	3349	4575	.	+	0	ID=MGA_3373;product=polysulfide reductase NrfD;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_005810041.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_33290;gene=nrfD;note=WP_005810041.1 polysulfide reductase NrfD (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:43.1%25%2C q_cov:76.0%25%2C s_cov:75.1%25%2C Eval:7.7e-66],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:38-404%2C Eval:3.5e-32%2C score:123.0],MGA_3373
