NODE_102_length_4093_cov_61.046813	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	142	1263	.	-	0	ID=MGA_3431;product=agmatine deiminase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_003104504.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_33750;gene=aguA;EC_number=3.5.3.12;note=WP_003104504.1 agmatine deiminase (Pseudomonas) [pid:50.3%25%2C q_cov:96.2%25%2C s_cov:97.8%25%2C Eval:1.7e-109],Domain:cl19186:Amidinotransf Amidinotransferase. Peptidyl-arginine deiminase (PAD) enzymes catalyze the deimination of the guanidino group from carboxy-terminal arginine residues of various peptides to produce ammonia. PAD from Porphyromonas gingivalis (PPAD) appears to be evolutionarily unrelated to mammalian PAD (pfam03068)%2C which is a metalloenzyme. PPAD is thought to belong to the same superfamily as aminotransferase and arginine deiminase%2C and to form an alpha/beta propeller structure. This family has previously been named PPADH (Porphyromonas peptidyl-arginine deiminase homologs). The predicted catalytic residues in PPAD are Asp130%2C Asp187%2C His236%2C Asp238 and Cys351. These are absolutely conserved with the exception of Asp187 which is absent in two family members. PPAD is also able to catalyze the deimination of free L-arginine%2C but has primarily peptidyl-arginine specificity. It may have a FMN cofactor. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:6-365%2C Eval:2.9e-134%2C score:384.8],MGA_3431
