NODE_115_length_3698_cov_51.520574	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	670	1065	.	-	0	ID=MGA_3462;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MCPTGATTKDEETGIVSVDSELCIGCESCIKACPYEGVRTLIKSPEYYLDVVVGEYDAPPHKGGTVEKCTFCKNLIDRGDVPACMQLCPGRARYWGDLDDPESDVSKAIEGRETMFLNEEAGTKPSVYYLQ;locus_tag=LOCUS_33980;note=WP_011460818.1 4Fe-4S dicluster domain-containing protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:59.2%25%2C q_cov:98.5%25%2C s_cov:63.1%25%2C Eval:1.8e-39%2C partial hit],internal stop codon at [1093:1095](-),TIGR:TIGR03149%3B cyt_nit_nrfC: cytochrome c nitrite reductase%2C Fe-S protein [Name:TIGR03149%2C Eval:1.0e-27%2C score:94.9%2C bias:2.0],Domain:cl25360:DMSOR_beta-like Beta subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. This family consists of the small beta iron-sulfur (FeS) subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. Members of this family also contain a large%2C periplasmic molybdenum-containing alpha subunit and may have a small gamma subunit as well.  Examples of heterodimeric members with alpha and beta subunits include arsenite oxidase%2C and tungsten-containing formate dehydrogenase (FDH-T) while   heterotrimeric members containing alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits include formate dehydrogenase-N (FDH-N)%2C and nitrate reductase (NarGHI).  The beta subunit contains four Fe4/S4 and/or Fe3/S4 clusters which transfer the electrons from the alpha subunit to a hydrophobic integral membrane protein%2C presumably a cytochrome containing two b-type heme groups. The reducing equivalents are then transferred to menaquinone%2C which finally reduces the electron-accepting enzyme system. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:2-130%2C Eval:3.3e-32%2C score:110.2%2C N-term missing],MGA_3462
